<br>
Anyway, enough ranting.  I think everyone should read this post and understand the puller's point of view.  It would help groups immensely! <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
I would like to add one thing, though... if a ranger or pally or some other non-pure caster class is using spells, and not going oom constantly so they can't do their main job, leave them be with their casting.  Unless of course they are interfering with things.  When I played a ranger at one point, occasionally casting was the butter on my bread <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   It broke up the monotony of tanking, for me.<br>
<br>
Just my 2 cents worth, here.<br>
<br>
Lindahl <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#A0B0E0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub29.ezboard.com/ugossimerwhitewing.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gossimer Whitewing</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 35<br> <font color=#A0B0E0>(5/8/01 4:33:53 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub29.ezboard.com/fsilverhawksofdrinalfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=24.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The art of pulling</span><hr size=1> I agree with the post. He knows how to play. Everyone has a job to do in a group. When one fails in their assignment, the entire group will more than likely die.<br>
<br>
When I play Goss, I never try to use any spells during battle. I am a backup healer and prebattler buffer. I try to save  my mana for those times. I will repeatly stun a target if I am fighting a spell caster. This I believe in the long run saves down time by stopping incoming damage before it happens. Also, I will at times cast root to stop multi mops when snare is not available.<br>
<br>
Everyone has a job and should know how to do it. The Hawks, I beleive, are some of the best players around, and as of to day I have never had a problem with any of you. (I would say you're all professionals, but who gets paid for playing EQ?)<br>
<br>
Just some thoughts.<br>
